  <Docs since="1">
    <summary>
      <c>Condition</c> factors out the <c>Object</c> monitor
 methods (<see cref="M:Java.Lang.Object.Wait" />, <see cref="M:Java.Lang.Object.Notify" />
 and <see cref="M:Java.Lang.Object.NotifyAll" />) into distinct objects to
 give the effect of having multiple wait-sets per object, by
 combining them with the use of arbitrary <see cref="T:Java.Util.Concurrent.Locks.ILock" /> implementations.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/locks/Condition" title="Reference documentation">Android platform documentation</a>
